<p>I can see where you get that vibe Sensei, but given that the population of 752 behaves monstrously I don't think this is piece is praising what we could become if we behaved differently. If there's any moral to be derived here it would be a cautionary one.</p>
<p>I have a hard time believing that a non-individual hive society would evolve/innovate/advance faster than our own, though—look at ants. Ants have been doing their thing for longer than humans have existed. They're such a successful part of the ecology that they are pretty stable evolution-wise. A society like the one described in 752 has no need to advance their technology quickly.</p>

